Does anyone happen to know how I would go about planning a maneuver between two stars? The trajectory always cuts off at Kerbol's SOI, so I can't see the rest of the trajectory going from Kerbol to Nova Kerbani.

On 2/26/2023 at 9:21 AM, intelliCom said:

Does anyone happen to know how I would go about planning a maneuver between two stars? The trajectory always cuts off at Kerbol's SOI, so I can't see the rest of the trajectory going from Kerbol to Nova Kerbani.

The best/easiest option (from videos I've seen online, I haven't attempted it yet) seems to be to burn directly towards Nova Kirbani despite the enormous amount of fuel and dV required. I'd imagine that you could do a Hohmann transfer instead, but I'd think it take an absurd period of time to complete the transfer (not just the burn), so there seems to be a trade-off between the two options.

Also, I've had issues with trying to successfully open KSP with GU installed. I've tried many times recently to get the mod to work, however it just isn't working for me. It always crashes when Breaking Ground starts to load, with a Unity error message appearing sometimes when the game crashes. I've installed GU with CKAN, reinstalled KSP and disabled the Steam Cloud to try and get it to work to no avail, which is why I'm making the post. I'm unsure on where to find my KSP logs which should help to troubleshoot the issue, so if someone could tell me how to send them it'd be perfect. As a point of reference, I've installed OPM from CKAN and it successfully ran after having similar issues initially after I had manually installed it and then allowed for CKAN to replace the manually installed files, however this technique did not work with GU. A solution would be appreciated ASAP.

I had the same issue yesterday, I installed GU systems one by one on CKAN to test which would run (Singularity crashes the game as of now btw) and found that after a certain amount of systems were downloaded, no matter which ones I had installed, the game would crash at a similar point to yours. I found that if you pick and choose which ones to have downloaded and are under that "limit" the game runs. I think it's a RAM limitation, because I've looked at my resource usage and when the game crashes it bricks my computer for a few seconds because my RAM is so under load. I have 16 GB and that doesn't cut it for more than 4/5 systems/expansions- the game uses something like 12gb on startup, peaking when it crashes. The less systems I had downloaded, the less RAM the game used. I've been looking into getting more RAM recently anyway, so maybe this will fix the problem. Hope this helps
